{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01XiVqK2VNS4NU8f4XP8KSgC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LaPgfWDqyBMT1yyJuScJjc","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# RabbitMQ Cluster — Upgrade & Configuration Migration Plan\n\n**Namespace:** `karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-af2b323e-cluster-a`\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-18\n**Status:** PLANNING ONLY — no changes applied. Live cluster left exactly as found.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State (as inspected)\n\n### Topology & Platform\n- **Workload:** StatefulSet `rabbitmq`, 3/3 replicas (`rabbitmq-0..2`), all Running.\n  - `updateStrategy: RollingUpdate`, `podManagementPolicy: OrderedReady`.\n- **Image:** `rabbitmq:3.12-management` → resolved version **RabbitMQ 3.12.14 on Erlang/OTP 25 (erts 13.2.2.11 / 25.3.2.15)**.\n- **Release support:** RabbitMQ **3.12 series is OUT OF SUPPORT** (per node status output). This is the primary driver for the upgrade.\n- **Cluster:** 3 disk nodes, all Running, no maintenance, **no alarms**.\n- **Storage:** No PVCs returned in namespace — data appears to be on `emptyDir`/ephemeral volumes (mnesia under `/var/lib/rabbitmq/mnesia`). **Verify before upgrade** — ephemeral storage means a full StatefulSet replace would lose definitions/messages.\n- **Plugins enabled:** `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_management_agent`, `rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common`, `rabbitmq_web_dispatch`.\n\n### Virtual Hosts\n| vhost | purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `/`   | default (admin only) |\n| `/app`| application traffic |\n| `/ops`| operations traffic |\n\n### Users & Permissions\n| user | tags | permissions |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `admin` | administrator | full `.* .* .*` on `/`, `/app`, `/ops` |\n| `app-user` | management | full `.* .* .*` on `/app` |\n| `ops-user` | management | full `.* .* .*` on `/ops` |\n\n### Policies\n| vhost | name | pattern | apply-to | definition | priority |\n|-------|------|---------|----------|------------|----------|\n| `/app` | `ha-all` | `^app-queue$` | queues | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |\n| `/` , `/ops` | (none) | | | | |\n\n### Queues\n| vhost | queue | type | durable | arguments |\n|-------|-------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | true | `x-queue-type=classic` |\n| `/ops` | `ops-queue` | classic | true | `x-queue-type=classic` |\n\n### Feature Flags\nAll flags **enabled**, including `quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`, `classic_mirrored_queue_version`, `feature_flags_v2`, `virtual_host_metadata`, `user_limits`. (All-enabled is a precondition for upgrading to the next minor.)\n\n---\n\n## 2. KEY RISK — Classic Mirrored Queues\n\nThe `/app` policy **`ha-all`** uses `ha-mode: all` — this is **classic queue mirroring (HA)**.\n\n- Classic mirroring is **deprecated in 3.13** and **removed in RabbitMQ 4.0**.\n- The `classic_mirrored_queue_version` feature flag and any `ha-*` policy must be retired before reaching 4.x.\n- `app-queue` is an explicitly classic queue mirrored by this policy.\n\n**This is the central migration item.** The recommended target is to migrate `app-queue` to a **quorum queue** (the supported replacement for HA classic queues). Quorum queues cannot be converted in place — they require create-new + drain/republish.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Recommended Upgrade Path\n\nRabbitMQ supports upgrades only between **adjacent minor versions**. Do not jump 3.12 → 4.0 directly.\n\n```\n3.12.14  →  3.13.x (latest patch)  →  4.0.x  →  4.1.x (target)\n```\n\n### Phase 0 — Pre-flight (no downtime)\n1. Confirm **all feature flags enabled** (already true) — required before each minor bump.\n2. **Confirm persistence:** verify mnesia data survives pod restart. If on `emptyDir`, FIRST migrate the StatefulSet to PVC-backed `volumeClaimTemplates` (separate change) — otherwise a rolling upgrade that recreates pods risks data loss.\n3. Export full definitions backup: `rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/defs.json` (or via management API) and copy off-cluster.\n4. Snapshot current state (this document) and stop non-essential producers if a maintenance window allows.\n\n### Phase 1 — Upgrade 3.12.14 → 3.13.x\n- Bump image to `rabbitmq:3.13-management` (pin a specific patch, e.g. `3.13.7-management`).\n- Rolling restart honoring `OrderedReady` (pods restart `rabbitmq-2` → `-1` → `-0`); wait for each node to fully rejoin (`rabbitmqctl cluster_status`, no alarms, queues synced) before the next.\n- After all nodes on 3.13: re-run `rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all`.\n- 3.13 still supports mirroring (deprecated) — cluster remains functional. **Mirroring removal happens here, before 4.0.**\n\n### Phase 2 — Remove classic mirroring / migrate `app-queue`\n- Create a new quorum queue (e.g. `app-queue-qq`) in `/app` with `x-queue-type: quorum`.\n- Repoint producers/consumers, drain `app-queue`, then delete the old queue and the `ha-all` policy. (Alternatively shovel messages across.)\n- Confirm no `ha-*` policies and no mirrored queues remain (`rabbitmqctl list_policies`, management UI \"Queues\" shows no mirrors).\n\n### Phase 3 — Upgrade 3.13.x → 4.0.x → 4.1.x\n- Repeat the rolling-restart procedure per minor bump; enable all feature flags after each.\n- 4.0 requires mirroring already gone (Phase 2) and all flags enabled.\n- Validate after each step: cluster_status, no alarms, all vhosts/users/permissions/queues present, app + ops traffic healthy.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Configuration Migration Checklist (to reapply / verify post-upgrade)\n- [ ] vhosts: `/`, `/app`, `/ops` present.\n- [ ] users: `admin` (administrator), `app-user` (management), `ops-user` (management) with passwords/permissions intact.\n- [ ] permissions: admin on all three vhosts; app-user on `/app`; ops-user on `/ops`.\n- [ ] queues: `ops-queue` (classic, durable) present; `app-queue` migrated to quorum (Phase 2).\n- [ ] policies: `ha-all` **removed** after migration; add a quorum-queue policy if HA semantics still needed (quorum queues are inherently replicated — usually no policy required).\n- [ ] plugins all re-enabled; Prometheus scraping intact (`prometheus` pod present in namespace).\n- [ ] feature flags all enabled.\n\n## 5. Rollback\n- Per minor: if a node fails to rejoin, halt the rolling upgrade, restore the failed node from the prior image, and verify cluster_status. RabbitMQ does **not** support in-place downgrade across minors — rollback = redeploy prior image + `import_definitions` from the Phase 0 backup into a freshly initialized cluster.\n- Keep the Phase 0 definitions export and (if PVC-backed) a volume snapshot for the duration of the change window.\n\n## 6. Recommended Change-Window Sequence (summary)\n1. Backup definitions + confirm persistence.\n2. 3.12 → 3.13, enable flags.\n3. Migrate `app-queue` to quorum, drop `ha-all`.\n4. 3.13 → 4.0 → 4.1, enabling flags each step.\n5. Run full config checklist + smoke test app/ops traffic.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":750,"cache_read_input_tokens":32696,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":750},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"44e6dfac-0ec9-45b2-886e-182cc5adedd3","uuid":"b77a3f64-87c0-41ed-a108-edeaec84e8d0","request_id":"req_011CcAdgCz6VfvPzQTWBwUTy"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LaPgfWDqyBMT1yyJuScJjc","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /tmp/plan.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"44e6dfac-0ec9-45b2-886e-182cc5adedd3","uuid":"ad23de73-e51b-499f-ae37-6456c48a74f0","timestamp":"2026-06-18T11:19:01.363Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# RabbitMQ Cluster — Upgrade & Configuration Migration Plan\n\n**Namespace:** `karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-af2b323e-cluster-a`\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-18\n**Status:** PLANNING ONLY — no changes applied. Live cluster left exactly as found.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State (as inspected)\n\n### Topology & Platform\n- **Workload:** StatefulSet `rabbitmq`, 3/3 replicas (`rabbitmq-0..2`), all Running.\n  - `updateStrategy: RollingUpdate`, `podManagementPolicy: OrderedReady`.\n- **Image:** `rabbitmq:3.12-management` → resolved version **RabbitMQ 3.12.14 on Erlang/OTP 25 (erts 13.2.2.11 / 25.3.2.15)**.\n- **Release support:** RabbitMQ **3.12 series is OUT OF SUPPORT** (per node status output). This is the primary driver for the upgrade.\n- **Cluster:** 3 disk nodes, all Running, no maintenance, **no alarms**.\n- **Storage:** No PVCs returned in namespace — data appears to be on `emptyDir`/ephemeral volumes (mnesia under `/var/lib/rabbitmq/mnesia`). **Verify before upgrade** — ephemeral storage means a full StatefulSet replace would lose definitions/messages.\n- **Plugins enabled:** `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_management_agent`, `rabbitmq_prometheus`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common`, `rabbitmq_web_dispatch`.\n\n### Virtual Hosts\n| vhost | purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `/`   | default (admin only) |\n| `/app`| application traffic |\n| `/ops`| operations traffic |\n\n### Users & Permissions\n| user | tags | permissions |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `admin` | administrator | full `.* .* .*` on `/`, `/app`, `/ops` |\n| `app-user` | management | full `.* .* .*` on `/app` |\n| `ops-user` | management | full `.* .* .*` on `/ops` |\n\n### Policies\n| vhost | name | pattern | apply-to | definition | priority |\n|-------|------|---------|----------|------------|----------|\n| `/app` | `ha-all` | `^app-queue$` | queues | `{\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}` | 0 |\n| `/` , `/ops` | (none) | | | | |\n\n### Queues\n| vhost | queue | type | durable | arguments |\n|-------|-------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | true | `x-queue-type=classic` |\n| `/ops` | `ops-queue` | classic | true | `x-queue-type=classic` |\n\n### Feature Flags\nAll flags **enabled**, including `quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`, `classic_mirrored_queue_version`, `feature_flags_v2`, `virtual_host_metadata`, `user_limits`. (All-enabled is a precondition for upgrading to the next minor.)\n\n---\n\n## 2. KEY RISK — Classic Mirrored Queues\n\nThe `/app` policy **`ha-all`** uses `ha-mode: all` — this is **classic queue mirroring (HA)**.\n\n- Classic mirroring is **deprecated in 3.13** and **removed in RabbitMQ 4.0**.\n- The `classic_mirrored_queue_version` feature flag and any `ha-*` policy must be retired before reaching 4.x.\n- `app-queue` is an explicitly classic queue mirrored by this policy.\n\n**This is the central migration item.** The recommended target is to migrate `app-queue` to a **quorum queue** (the supported replacement for HA classic queues). Quorum queues cannot be converted in place — they require create-new + drain/republish.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Recommended Upgrade Path\n\nRabbitMQ supports upgrades only between **adjacent minor versions**. Do not jump 3.12 → 4.0 directly.\n\n```\n3.12.14  →  3.13.x (latest patch)  →  4.0.x  →  4.1.x (target)\n```\n\n### Phase 0 — Pre-flight (no downtime)\n1. Confirm **all feature flags enabled** (already true) — required before each minor bump.\n2. **Confirm persistence:** verify mnesia data survives pod restart. If on `emptyDir`, FIRST migrate the StatefulSet to PVC-backed `volumeClaimTemplates` (separate change) — otherwise a rolling upgrade that recreates pods risks data loss.\n3. Export full definitions backup: `rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/defs.json` (or via management API) and copy off-cluster.\n4. Snapshot current state (this document) and stop non-essential producers if a maintenance window allows.\n\n### Phase 1 — Upgrade 3.12.14 → 3.13.x\n- Bump image to `rabbitmq:3.13-management` (pin a specific patch, e.g. `3.13.7-management`).\n- Rolling restart honoring `OrderedReady` (pods restart `rabbitmq-2` → `-1` → `-0`); wait for each node to fully rejoin (`rabbitmqctl cluster_status`, no alarms, queues synced) before the next.\n- After all nodes on 3.13: re-run `rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all`.\n- 3.13 still supports mirroring (deprecated) — cluster remains functional. **Mirroring removal happens here, before 4.0.**\n\n### Phase 2 — Remove classic mirroring / migrate `app-queue`\n- Create a new quorum queue (e.g. `app-queue-qq`) in `/app` with `x-queue-type: quorum`.\n- Repoint producers/consumers, drain `app-queue`, then delete the old queue and the `ha-all` policy. (Alternatively shovel messages across.)\n- Confirm no `ha-*` policies and no mirrored queues remain (`rabbitmqctl list_policies`, management UI \"Queues\" shows no mirrors).\n\n### Phase 3 — Upgrade 3.13.x → 4.0.x → 4.1.x\n- Repeat the rolling-restart procedure per minor bump; enable all feature flags after each.\n- 4.0 requires mirroring already gone (Phase 2) and all flags enabled.\n- Validate after each step: cluster_status, no alarms, all vhosts/users/permissions/queues present, app + ops traffic healthy.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Configuration Migration Checklist (to reapply / verify post-upgrade)\n- [ ] vhosts: `/`, `/app`, `/ops` present.\n- [ ] users: `admin` (administrator), `app-user` (management), `ops-user` (management) with passwords/permissions intact.\n- [ ] permissions: admin on all three vhosts; app-user on `/app`; ops-user on `/ops`.\n- [ ] queues: `ops-queue` (classic, durable) present; `app-queue` migrated to quorum (Phase 2).\n- [ ] policies: `ha-all` **removed** after migration; add a quorum-queue policy if HA semantics still needed (quorum queues are inherently replicated — usually no policy required).\n- [ ] plugins all re-enabled; Prometheus scraping intact (`prometheus` pod present in namespace).\n- [ ] feature flags all enabled.\n\n## 5. Rollback\n- Per minor: if a node fails to rejoin, halt the rolling upgrade, restore the failed node from the prior image, and verify cluster_status. RabbitMQ does **not** support in-place downgrade across minors — rollback = redeploy prior image + `import_definitions` from the Phase 0 backup into a freshly initialized cluster.\n- Keep the Phase 0 definitions export and (if PVC-backed) a volume snapshot for the duration of the change window.\n\n## 6. Recommended Change-Window Sequence (summary)\n1. Backup definitions + confirm persistence.\n2. 3.12 → 3.13, enable flags.\n3. Migrate `app-queue` to quorum, drop `ha-all`.\n4. 3.13 → 4.0 → 4.1, enabling flags each step.\n5. Run full config checklist + smoke test app/ops traffic.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
